# Project Structure — Shortly

A React + Vite URL shortening app (Frontend Mentor challenge) using Tailwind CSS v4, DaisyUI 5, and React Router 7. Deployed to GitHub Pages via `gh-pages`.

## Root Files

```
PROJECT_ROOT/
├── index.html              # Vite entry HTML
├── package.json            # pnpm project — scripts: dev, build, lint, deploy
├── vite.config.js          # Vite config — @/ alias → ./src, SWC plugin
├── postcss.config.js       # PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss
├── .eslintrc.cjs           # ESLint (standard + prettier + react rules)
├── .prettierrc.json        # Prettier config
├── jsconfig.json           # Path alias support for editors
├── style-guide.md          # Frontend Mentor design spec (colors, fonts, breakpoints)
├── .todo                   # Project TODO tracker
└── README.md
```

## Source Directory (`src/`)

```
src/
├── main.jsx                # ReactDOM entry point
├── App.jsx                 # Root component — wraps ThemeContext + UrlContext + AppRouter
├── index.css               # Global styles, Tailwind imports, CSS custom properties
├── assets/
│   ├── font/               # Poppins font files (.ttf): Regular, Medium, MediumItalic, SemiBold, Bold
│   └── img/                # SVG assets (backgrounds, icons, illustrations, logo)
│       └── index.js        # Barrel export for all images
├── router/
│   └── AppRouter.jsx       # React Router config — BrowserRouter with PublicLayout + HomePage
├── pages/
│   └── HomePage.jsx        # Main landing page composing brand + url-shortening sections
└── modules/                # Feature-based module architecture (see below)
```

## Module Architecture (`src/modules/`)

The app follows a **feature-module pattern** with three modules:

### `core/` — Shared infrastructure & reusable components

```
modules/core/
├── api/
│   ├── clients/
│   │   └── client-fetch.js           # Fetch API wrapper
│   └── hooks/
│       └── use-fetch.js              # Custom hook for data fetching
├── components/
│   ├── base/                         # Base (reusable) UI components
│   │   ├── BaseButton.jsx
│   │   ├── BaseCard.jsx
│   │   ├── BaseDivider.jsx
│   │   ├── BaseInput.jsx
│   │   └── BaseThemeSwitch.jsx
│   └── layout/                       # Layout shell components
│       ├── LayoutFooter.jsx
│       ├── LayoutHeader.jsx
│       └── LayoutHeaderMobileMenu.jsx
├── constants/
│   └── index.js                      # App-wide constants (nav links, footer links, social links, etc.)
├── context/
│   └── context-theme.jsx             # Theme context provider (light/dark)
├── hooks/
│   ├── use-context-check.js          # Context existence validator
│   ├── use-input.js                  # Form input state hook
│   ├── use-local-storage.js          # LocalStorage read/write hook
│   └── use-theme.js                  # Theme consumer hook
├── layouts/
│   └── PublicLayout.jsx              # Page layout (Header + Outlet + Footer)
└── utils/
    └── cn.js                         # clsx + tailwind-merge utility
```

### `brand/` — Marketing / static content sections

```
modules/brand/
└── components/
    ├── banner/
    │   └── BannerCta.jsx             # CTA banner ("Boost your links today")
    ├── card/
    │   └── CardFeature.jsx           # Feature highlight card
    └── section/
        ├── SectionFeatures.jsx       # "Advanced Statistics" section with feature cards
        └── SectionHero.jsx           # Hero section with illustration
```

### `url-shortening/` — Core URL shortening feature

```
modules/url-shortening/
├── api/
│   ├── hooks/
│   │   ├── use-get-url-list.js       # Hook to retrieve saved shortened URLs
│   │   ├── use-save-url-list.js      # Hook to persist shortened URLs
│   │   └── use-short-url.js          # Hook to call shortening API
│   ├── providers/
│   │   ├── provider-url-shortener-fetch.js        # Remote API provider
│   │   └── provider-url-shortener-localstorage.js # LocalStorage persistence provider
│   └── services/
│       └── service-url-shortener.js  # Service layer orchestrating providers
├── components/
│   ├── form/
│   │   └── FormUrl.jsx               # URL input form with validation
│   ├── list/
│   │   ├── ListShortenedUrls.jsx     # Shortened URL results list
│   │   └── ListShortenedUrlsItem.jsx # Individual shortened URL item with copy button
│   └── section/
│       └── SectionShortenUrl.jsx     # Section composing form + list
└── contexts/
    └── context-url.jsx               # URL list context provider
```

## Key Conventions

1. **Path alias**: `@/` maps to `src/` (configured in `vite.config.js` and `jsconfig.json`)
2. **Component naming**: PascalCase filenames matching the component name (e.g., `BaseButton.jsx`)
3. **Hook naming**: kebab-case with `use-` prefix (e.g., `use-fetch.js`)
4. **Module organization**: Each module groups its own `api/`, `components/`, `contexts/`, `hooks/` as needed
5. **Barrel exports**: Image assets use `index.js` barrel files; components are imported directly by path
6. **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 + DaisyUI 5 component classes + CSS custom properties in `index.css`
7. **Package manager**: pnpm (see `pnpm-lock.yaml`)
8. **Deployment**: GitHub Pages via `gh-pages` package — base path `/shortly/` in production

## Static Assets

- **`public/`**: Contains only `favicon-32x32.png`
- **`src/assets/img/`**: All SVG illustrations, icons, and backgrounds with barrel export via `index.js`
- **`src/assets/font/`**: Self-hosted Poppins font family (5 weights)

## Config Files

- **`.vscode/settings.json`**: Editor-specific settings
- **`.cursor/rules/`**: AI assistant rules (this file, `cursor-rules.mdc`, `components-guide.mdc`, `self-improvement.mdc`)
- **`.env`**: Environment variables (API keys, base URLs)
